Package: hovR
Type: Package
Title: Drone Hyperspectral Time-Series Analysis
Version: 0.2.0
Date: 2026-04-19
Authors@R: c(
    person("hovR", "Contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "contact@dronehsi.dev")
  )
Description: End-to-end tools for drone-based hyperspectral image and
    time-series analysis. The package covers four tightly integrated modules:
    (1) Temporal integration — stacking multi-date hyperspectral rasters into
    a FlightStack, computing seasonal VI integrals (AUC), temporal derivatives,
    optimal flight windows, and BBCH phenological stage tagging;
    (2) Plot auto-segmentation — detecting and delineating trial plot boundaries
    directly from drone imagery without manual polygon drawing, with support for
    regular grids, staggered rows, and irregular layouts;
    (3) Calibration panel detection — automatically locating grey calibration
    panels in flight images and applying empirical-line reflectance calibration,
    eliminating per-flight manual panel clicking;
    (4) Flight quality assessment — automated per-flight QC checks (blur,
    saturation, irradiance stability, no-data fraction) with structured
    accept/caution/reject recommendations and an HTML report generator.
    Together these modules replace days of manual GIS work and hours of
    per-flight calibration with single function calls.
